# Styling (Uniwind)

Neuland Next uses **Uniwind** (Tailwind CSS v4 for React Native). Use `className` on React Native primitives.

## Essentials

- **Entry**: `src/global.css` imported in `src/app/_layout.tsx` (never in Expo `index`)
- **Metro**: `metro.config.js` — `withUniwindConfig` must be the outermost wrapper
- **Tokens**: `@theme` + `@layer theme` / `@variant light|dark` in `global.css`; mirror `src/styles/themes.ts`
- **Theme sync**: `useUniwindThemeSync` in `provider.tsx` — do not duplicate preference logic
- **Helpers**: `@/utils/uniwind-utils` (`hairlineBorder`, `toColor`)
- **Styled wrappers**: `@/components/Universal/styled` for FlashList, BottomSheet, expo-image
- **Types**: run `bun uniwind:types` after changing `global.css`

```tsx
// Typical pattern
<View className="bg-card border border-border rounded-lg p-page">
  <Text className="text-text text-base">…</Text>
</View>
```

- Platform variants: `ios:`, `android:`, `web:`
- Runtime colors: `useCSSVariable('--color-primary')` from `uniwind`
- Dark mode check: `useUniwind()` → `theme === 'dark'`
- Style props for third-party children: `useResolveClassNames('text-text text-base')`
- Keep inline `style` for: Reanimated, dynamic dimensions, hairline borders, dynamic per-item colors

## Avoid

- `react-native-unistyles`, NativeWind, styled-components, or raw Tailwind config files outside `global.css`
- Hard-coded colors/sizes — use theme tokens
- Editing `src/uniwind-types.d.ts` by hand
- Importing `global.css` in the Expo entry file (breaks HMR)

